\b Trait Random Elements
\b0 ---------\
\
[List] adds a random Trait from the List in brackets. 
\fs22 (Example: "[Gnome First Name]killer the Criminal Guy" might give you "Jerkkiller the Criminal Guy" or "Laserkiller the Criminal Guy".)
\fs24 \
\
\{A | B | C\} picks one of the options.
\fs22  Thats the straight line underneath the backspace key. You can have as many options as you want with a bar between each option. (Example: "\{King|Queen\}hater" could give you "Kinghater" or "Queenhater.)
\fs24 \
\
` is a blank option.
\fs22  It's useful for a blank list item (to allow humans to have no middle name, put ` as a separate line on the 
\i Middle Name
\i0  list.) or as a blank option in braces. "\{Professor|Dr.|`\} James" allows your teacher to be named "Dr. James", "Professor James", or just "James". 
\fs24 \
\
These items can be combined. 
\fs22 \{[Gnome Name]|[Elf Name]\}hater will create a criminal that either hates a particular gnome or a particular elf (ex. Lasterhater or Rose-leafhater)
