\b Name Format
\b0 -------------\
\
This is one of the things I added because I didn't think about other people using it. You leave it blank and still use the program just fine. The program will try to guess what the NPC's name is so it can display that as the title. (It makes it look a lot nicer). This is how you explicitly tell it what to put as the name. \

\fs22 \
All Aspects and Lists have a type. The type is just a phrase like "Full Name" or "Personality". Aspects and Lists will replace earlier Aspects & Lists with the same type (so your NPC only has one personality, and so your American Human can have an American Name instead of a generic Human Name.). \
	You can change the type by right clicking in the menu while viewing the contents of that Aspect or List and selecting "Change List Type".\
\
All Templates have one Name Format. The Name Format is a short list of types. "First Name, Middle Name, Last Name, Title". That tells the program that the display title for that NPC should be its full name. You can do a single type like "Full Name".\
	You can change the Name Format by right clicking in the template menu when viewing the contents of that Template and selecting "Change Name Format". \
